<topic template="Default" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Intoroduction</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Introduction</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Intoroduction</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is a BIM collaboration toolkit compatible with &#160;Revit, Naviswords, AutoCad, ArchiCad, SketchUp, Rhinoceros for Windows. </text><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> allows project members to :</text></para>
    <list id="2" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullet_1" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">share project models and review them (game-like viewing and navigation options)</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">report, process and monitor issues</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">communicate in real time</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> toolkit includes:</text></para>
    <list id="3" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullet_1" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">plugins for every supported source tool to </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Exporting-Files-to-Revizto" styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">export source models</link></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">core application for viewing exported models, </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Issue-LifeCycle" styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">collaborating</link><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true"> and </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Project-Management2" styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">managing projects</link></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">web GUI for</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Licensing" styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true"> license management</link><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true"> and project management</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="VR-Options" styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">VR functionality </link></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">and many other options</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Bullet_1"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> relies on cloud technologies, so you can collaborate 24/7, worldwide. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Note that you can find additional product info and tutorials on our </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="weblink" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC7BkKc2oh5bQSStCgoAm-KA" target="_blank" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">YouTube channel</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="weblink" href="https://revizto.com" target="_blank" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">website</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
  </body>
